&ldquo;Kipple is useless objects, like junk mail or match folders after you use the last match or gum wrappers or yesterday&rsquo;s homeopape. When nobody&rsquo;s around, kipple reproduces itself. For instance, if you go to bed leaving any kipple around your apartment, when you wake up the next morning there&rsquo;s twice as much of it. It always gets more and more.&rdquo;
